"yhh" = (
/obj/structure/sign/kiddieplaque{
	desc = "===ARMAT SYSTEMS==\n==WEAPON MOD CATALOUGE==\n=March 2050 Edition=\n===Introduction===\n\nGreetings proud soldier of the United Americas!\n We at Armat Systems believe that soldiers operate best on the field when their gear suits them.\nTherefore, we have put together a comprehensive catalogue of the different field-modifcations to which you are likely to encounter in the field.\n\nPlease speak to your local supply officer about mail-in orders. \n\n\n ===BARREL MODS===\n\nSupressor: Used to silence weapons.\n Fits: M41a, M42c, m39, M4a3\n\nBayonet: Used to improve melee\nFits: M41a, M37, M4a3\n\nRecoil compensator: Lowers recoil, at the cost to power\nFits: M41c, M37\n\nExtended barrel: Higher accuracy, less power\nFits:M41a, M37, M39, M4a3, 44\n\nBarrel charger: Stronger impact damage, less accuracy, more recoil\nFits:M41a, M56 Smartgun, M37, M39, M4a3, 44\n\n===RAIL MODS===\n\n\nRail flashlight: General purpose flashlight mount. \nFits: M41a, M37, M39, M4a3\n\nRed-dot sight: Higher accuracy\nFits: M41a, M37, M39, M4a3, 44\n\nMag Harness: Weapon snaps to armor if dropped\nFits: M41a, M42c M39\n\nQuickfire Adapter: Weapon is able to fire quickly, less accuracy, more recoil\nFits: M41a, M37, M39, M4a3, 44\n\n\n===UNDERBARREL MODS===\n\nForward grip: Higher accuracy, less recoil. Need both hands, harder to carry. \nFits:M41a, M37, M39, M4a3\n\nGyroscope: Allows weapons to be fired with one hand, higher recoil and less accuracy\nFits: M41a, M37, M42c\n\nBipod: Gives the weapon more control, but at the cost of CQC ability and size. \nFits: M41a, M42c\n\nBurstfire: Improves upon the burst-fire capacity of a weapon, or enables it. \nFits: M41a, M39, M4a3\n\n There appears to be a photo of a Colonial Marine holding two attachments. He appears to be mentally handicapped. \n\n";
	name = "Armat Systems Modification Catalogue";
	pixel_y = 30
	},
/turf/open/floor/almayer/cargo_arrow,
/area/sulaco/cargo/office)
